[{"id":27539,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["Vitamin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","Vitamin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></math>","Vitamin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","Vitamin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Vitamin helpful in the blood clotting is Vitamin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>.</p><p>Vitamin K is a fat soluble vitamin&nbsp;required for normal blood clotting. Its deficiency leads to slow or delayed blood clotting and&nbsp;haemorrhage (blood loss). Vitamin K is&nbsp;required for synthesis of prothrombin in the liver&nbsp;where the vitamin K-dependent carboxylation in prothrombin synthesis occurs.</p><p>Note: Question has been&nbsp;slightly modified for its correctness.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27548,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["One ketal and one hemiketal","Two acetals","One acetal and one hemiacetal","One acetal and one ketal"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bc057365-8923-44b6-9a96-af8da96ea507-image.png\" style=\"width: 409px; height: 181px;\" /></p><p>Cyclic hemiacetal are formed when an alcohol oxygen atom adds to the carbonyl carbon of an aldehyde or a ketone. Molecules (aldehyde or ketone), which contain both an alcohol and a carbonyl group, can instead undergo an intramolecular reaction to form a cyclic hemiacetal/ hemiketal.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27405,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["A-I, B-III, C-II, D-IV","A-I, B-III, C-IV, D-II","A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II","A-III, B-I, C-II, D-IV"],"answer":2,"solution":"Scurvy is caused by the deficiency of Vitamin C, which is chemically known as Ascorbic acid. Thus, A matches with III.<br><br>Convulsions are caused by the deficiency of Vitamin B6, which is chemically known as Pyridoxine. Thus, B matches with I.<br><br>Cheilosis (fissuring at corners of mouth and lips) is caused by the deficiency of Vitamin B2, which is chemically known as Riboflavin. Thus, C matches with IV.<br><br>Xerophthalmia (hardening of cornea of eye) is caused by the deficiency of Vitamin A. Thus, D matches with II.<br><br>The correct matching is A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II.<br><br>Answer: A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27495,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>A) On prolonged heating with HI, Glucose&nbsp;forms n-hexane, suggesting that all the six carbon atoms are linked in a straight chain.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d89972e-6b06-4b5a-9f82-3229ddcd6726-image.png\" style=\"width: 251px; height: 33px;\" /></p><p>B) Glucose gets oxidised to six carbon carboxylic acid (gluconic acid) on reaction with a mild oxidising agent like bromine water. This indicates that the carbonyl group is present as an aldehydic group.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9a2cfdec-407a-4dec-b4a2-794393ed60aa-image.png\" style=\"width: 283px; height: 120px;\" />C) Acetylation of glucose with acetic anhydride gives glucose pentaacetate which confirms the presence of five &ndash;OH groups. Since it exists as a stable compound, five &ndash;OH groups should be attached to different carbon atoms.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6a6fc1ab-8b47-4286-9d0b-de5d5711fba0-12-08-2022newwws.png\" style=\"width: 309px; height: 131px;\" /></p><p>D) On oxidation with nitric acid, glucose as well as gluconic acid both yield a dicarboxylic acid, saccharic acid. This indicates the presence of a primary alcoholic (&ndash;OH) group in glucose</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dbe03e9d-dc88-41cd-bb2e-0a19b6c5014c-image.png\" style=\"width: 322px; height: 120px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27526,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["Fibrin","Albumin","Myosin","Collagen"],"answer":1,"solution":"Albumin is water soluble.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27521,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>All acidic groups loose a proton to form negative charge at pH = 12.5.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9e3b2c9e-4b09-45ba-82b0-d9d560da5508-image.png\" style=\"width: 965px; height: 212px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27575,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["cellulose and amylose has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage.","lactose contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo></math>galactose and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo></math>glucose.","maltose and lactose has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage.","sucrose and amylose has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage."],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>In amylose,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage is present.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8b891569-75c4-4e17-bf04-e6983085be01-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 170px;\" /><br />So, this option statement is incorrect.</p><p>Sucrose has 1,2-glycosidic linkage between glucose and fructose.&nbsp;</p>cellulose and amylose has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage. lactose contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo></math>galactose and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo></math>glucose. maltose and lactose has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>glycosidic linkage.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (16 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27560,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Biomolecules","question":"","options":["<math><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mn>4</mn></math>","<math><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mn>5</mn></math>","<math><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mn>5</mn></math>","<math><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"The respective structures are (with for stereocentres),<br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hguloqqbnypgxxytmqywpsmzkbfyjrmcjvvvlnkbuqjfwnhwzp.jpeg\" /><br /><br />Thus, no. of stereocentres respectively are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null}]